==English==

===Etymology===
From Persian {{FAchar|[[کاروانسرای]]}} (kārwānserāy), from {{FAchar|[[کاروان]]}} (kārvān) ‘caravan’ + {{FAchar|[[سرای]]}} (sarāy) ‘palace’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/kærəˈvænsəraɪ/}}

===Alternative spellings===
*[[caravansary]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[inn]] having a central courtyard where [[caravan]]s can rest

====Synonyms====
*[[khan]]

